org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.selector

接口 OutputSelector<OUT>

  • 类型参数:
    OUT - Type parameter of the split values.
    所有超级接口:
    java.io.Serializable
    所有已知实现类:
    IterateExample.MySelector, StormStreamSelector

    @PublicEvolving
public interface OutputSelector<OUT>
extends java.io.Serializable
    Interface for defining an OutputSelector for a SplitStream using the DataStream.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.selector.OutputSelector<T>) call. Every output object of a SplitStream will run through this operator to select outputs.

    • 方法概要

      所有方法 实例方法 抽象方法 
      限定符和类型 方法和说明
      java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> select(OUT value)
      Method for selecting output names for the emitted objects when using the DataStream.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.selector.OutputSelector<T>) method.

    • 方法详细资料

      • select

        java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> select(OUT value)
        Method for selecting output names for the emitted objects when using the DataStream.split(org.apache.flink.streaming.api.collector.selector.OutputSelector<T>) method. The values will be emitted only to output names which are contained in the returned iterable.
        参数:
        value - Output object for which the output selection should be made.
